  "texts": [
    "It is obvious that he considered consciousness as the emergent property of the mind, as a derivative of thought, and its relations to existence.",
    "Namely personality, intelligence, and perception of selfhood.",
    "\"I am\" is the dominant rule; and \"my\" thoughts are \"my\" elegant proof of \"my\" individuality, \"my identity\" [11].",
    "A newer approach which adds skepticism to the Descartian aphorism is the brain in a vat argument, which poses the question that if we are hooked up to a computer program that can perfectly simulate our perceived reality, we can never be sure that this is either a simulation, or reality [12].",
    "A possible solution to mitigate the culprit that a Deus Deceptor or \"an evil daemon\" constantly deceives us [13], is to have a set of witnesses who can attest and accept that our reality is their reality as well, so that \"together we know\" that our perceived manifestation of the world, is actually real."
  ],
